Returning to the exposition of our model, Efros and Shklovskii developed a scaling theory of the conductivity of a system where nodes were connected by either low conductivity bonds σlow, or high conductivity bonds σhigh. They proposed that a universal, critical crossover scaling function describes the system mobility as the increasing fraction of high mobility bonds percolate across the system:1σ/σhigh=(σlow/σhigh)sφ[(xc−x)/(σlow/σhigh)m]\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
